The paper deals with temporal action detection in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as classifiers and regression models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as text classification, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
